hopobject.body: Do you know the address? can you take a prescription to any pharmacy McCririck told BBC News at the Central London Employment Tribunal on Monday: "The Equality Act in 2010 said you cannot sack somebody because of their age, and there are hundreds of thousands of people in this country, in their 30s to their 70s, who dread, who fear the threat of the sack just because someone younger is chosen by one of the suits and skirts."
